entries.femaleVariant: Here we are.
What'd I say? Drives like a fuckin' cyberpsycho.
Now we wait.
There she is. Right on the dot.
What we ordered – musical gear.
What's inside?
Your lucky day, Ker. Crates 'n' crates of nothin' but gear.
Hell yeaaah, we got a hit!
Now for the grand finale. Want this set to be a smoldering puddle of chrome and plastic when we're done.
[Set up stinger]
Fuck, V, honestly?
No idea. Hope whatever happens, you'll be able to handle it.
You're the boss.
This your new signature move?
You're the boss.
Ah – new signature move?
Mhm, you got it. So don't miss.
Got your mixers, speakers, drums, cables by the mile.
Guys we're waitin' on – they armed?
You two whacked?! The hell was that?!
You got it.
Nice cache.
Those are police stingers and grenades. Where'd you get 'em?
Well, well... quite the arsenal.
We're fighting for art. Art with a capital A. C'mon, get to work.
Hm, I know the guy – this ain't about art.
C'mon, fess up. This a publicity stunt?
All right, just spit it out. This a set-up? Flock of medias about to fly in?
entries.maleVariant: All right, just spit it out. Is this a set-up? Is a flock of medias about to fly in?

entries.femaleVariant: Whoever's driving that truck – they armed, maybe? Got any huscle?
Stuff worth a couple hundred thou. Could be ours.
Stuff's worth at least a couple hundred thou'. Really wanna trash it, not klep it?
entries.maleVariant: Stuff's worth at least a couple hundred thou'. You really wanna trash it, not klep it?

entries.femaleVariant: Please... Never stolen a thing in my life.
Fuck me, he really believes that? I remember all my strings getting swiped back in the day. Never had his own.
Light 'er up.
Fuck me, Kerry.
Meanin', it's just a truck of toys for some plastic Japanese dolls. Might as well blow up a cotton candy stand, but...
Still a big step forward. I hardly recognize the bastard.
[Take card] Quit squirming.
Quit squirmin'. And no gonk moves.
Lay it out here.
[Hide] Now what?
[Take stinger and grenades] You got it.
What now?
H-hey, man, lose the iron. Let's talk it out.
Not a word. It'll all be over soon.
Ugh, fuckin' hell...
Access card, grab it!
Y'know they killed IV Coma right here, in this very spot? The DJ?
[Draw gun] Get out! On the ground!
Move, move! 'Less you want somethin' to happen to our friend here!
V, move! Don't have time.
Right, gents. Now run along and don't look back.
You drive. Get 'em off our ass.
Trunk. Grab what's in there.
Come on, set those spikes – today, maybe?
Showtime. I take the driver, you get his sidechoom. We want 'em outta the truck!
Sure hope you know what you're doin'.
Outta the truck, on the ground, hands where I can see 'em.
Get out! Ground, now!
Pop the back.
[Open]
Hahaha...! Fuck yeah!
Good workin' with ya, V!
Well, wouldn't it've been better to have a lawyer fight this fight for you?
entries.maleVariant: Wouldn't it've been better to have a lawyer fight this fight for ya?

entries.femaleVariant: This here? I'm sendin' a message. This is how you do biz in Night City.
Sick burn. But for what?
Considering a new career in terrorism?
Burnin' real nice, I'll grant you that. Thing is, I mean, what's it actually get you?
entries.maleVariant: It's burnin' real nice, I'll grant ya that. Thing is, I mean, what's it actually get ya?

entries.femaleVariant: Couldn't a lawyer do this better?
Woulda done the same. Props.
Cops. Let's delta.
Get out! On the ground!
Ah, scared two chooms shitless, flamed a truck... Tryin' to be the next Johnny Silverhand, Kerry? Play terrorist?
entries.maleVariant: Scared two chooms shitless, flamed a truck... Tryin' to be the next Johnny Silverhand, Kerry? Play terrorist?

entries.femaleVariant: You always oversimplify shit? Nuance, V. You say vandalism, I say artistic protest.
That is how you do biz in Night City. Respect, Ker.
entries.maleVariant: Heh, that's how you do biz in Night City. Respect, Ker.

entries.femaleVariant: Ya get me, finally. Thanks.
Turned out later she wasn't the target. Some Biotechnica suit, busy eatin' 'er out when the bullets started flyin'. Found the bodies... just like that.
Right. Hide. Quick.
Get out. Do what I say, everything'll be fine.
Get out. Nice 'n' easy, no weirdness, nothing'll happen.
entries.maleVariant: Get out. Nice and easy, no weirdness, nothing'll happen.

entries.femaleVariant: Hey, man, listen...
On the ground, I said!
I said, delta the fuck off!
Playin' by ear, huh? Ah, wouldn't be my first time.
entries.maleVariant: Playin' by ear, huh? Wouldn't be my first time.

entries.femaleVariant: Got the wrong truck! Fuck, we're not--
I said – easy. Now get down on the ground. Won't say it a third time.
Next me? Hah, please. Kerry's got a short fuse, sure, but ain't no dynamite in that soul.
Mmh. And the real reason?
If those little bitches think they can make it big on MY song, they got another thing comin'.
You even know what I had to sacrifice to get where I am? The price I paid for success?!
And those ten-enny whores wanna klep my tune and expect me to just let 'em?! Fucking pig-ignorant hacks.
Yeah, "success." Always a sore spot of Ker's. See nothing's changed.
Automated modules, hollow spikes for better control of the vehicle – standard-issue police tech. 'Nades, too. Where'd you get 'em?
Same place you get designer drugs, the latest, still-patent-pending AudioVox and fresh Yubaris.
Black market?
Nah – fans.
Oh, you're one to talk. I've flashed my teeth and signed papers enough for one lifetime.
Cloaked AV followed her limo. Almost nothin' left of 'er afterwards... or the limo.
Wouldn't mind that, actually.
Honestly, no idea what's about to go down. Just... improvise.
[Get out]
Ah, stay nice an' still there, boys.
Nuh-uh, calm and quiet. It'll be over soon.
Let's go, V! Pop 'er open!
Fuck, can't keep me on edge like this, V! Whadda we got there?
Get goin'!
Give those little bitches a taste of American hospitality. C'mon, V!
Waitin' for a special invite?
What the fuuuck?
Keep your traps shut, gents. No chatter.
[Get in]
